<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="307" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,900,838,898]" box="[151,900,838,864]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,900,838,864]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,900,838,864]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<taxonomicName box="[151,408,838,864]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Macrostemum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bravoi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,408,838,864]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Macrostemum bravoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry box="[416,507,838,864]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">França</collectingCountry>
, Paprocki &amp; Calor, new species
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,900,838,898]" box="[151,277,873,898]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<figureCitation box="[151,225,873,898]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,231,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1410,195,1950]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Macrostemum bravoi, new species. A, right fore- and hind wings, dorsal view; B – E, male genitalia: B, left lateral view; C, phallus, left lateral view; D, apex of phallus, ventral view; E, terga IX and X, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217689/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Figs. 
<number box="[213,225,874,898]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A–E
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,945,1981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
This new species has a distinct medial prominence on the anterior margin of its falciform phallotremal sclerite in ventral view. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[593,864,981,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Macrostemum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">
<emphasis box="[593,864,981,1005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Macrostemum erichsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the anterior margin of segment IX is rounded and the apex of the phallus is truncate in lateral view. The forewings of the new species have a distinctive pattern of hyaline and brownish areas with blurred boundaries while all previously described species have very well-defined dark spots. However, the distribution and the shape of the spots can resemble those of 
<emphasis box="[1118,1267,1089,1113]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<taxonomicName box="[1118,1263,1089,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Macrostemum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">M. erichsoni</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="307" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,945,1981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1125,1150]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Description.</emphasis>
Adults in alcohol. Forewing mean length 
<quantity box="[843,946,1126,1150]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.19" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" unit="mm" value="11.9">11.9 mm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[964,1161,1125,1150]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2075" metricValueMax="1.286" metricValueMin="1.129" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" unit="mm" value="12.075" valueMax="12.86" valueMin="11.29">11.29–12.86 mm</quantity>
, n= 
<number box="[1210,1225,1126,1150]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="7.0">7</number>
). Head yellowishbrown. Compound eyes black. Scapes brown dorsally and yellow on ventral surfaces. Maxillary palps yellow with ferruginous and yellow setae. Prothorax yellow. Meso- and metathorax yellowish-brown. Legs brownish-yellow. Tibial spur formula 1,4, 
<number box="[414,432,1234,1258]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="4.0">4</number>
. Forewings with dark and hyaline pattern colors; but spots without clearly distinguishable boundaries; each with discoidal cell present; radial sector normal (
<figureCitation box="[894,960,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,231,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1410,195,1950]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Macrostemum bravoi, new species. A, right fore- and hind wings, dorsal view; B – E, male genitalia: B, left lateral view; C, phallus, left lateral view; D, apex of phallus, ventral view; E, terga IX and X, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217689/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Fig. 
<number box="[946,960,1270,1294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,945,1981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Male genitalia. Abdominal segment IX, in lateral view, with anterior margin rounded; posterior margin sinuous, deeply notched, bordered by long setae above and below notch (
<figureCitation box="[993,1061,1341,1366]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,231,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1410,195,1950]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Macrostemum bravoi, new species. A, right fore- and hind wings, dorsal view; B – E, male genitalia: B, left lateral view; C, phallus, left lateral view; D, apex of phallus, ventral view; E, terga IX and X, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217689/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Fig. 
<number box="[1047,1061,1342,1366]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B); in dorsal view with posterior margin bearing medial acuminate keel and long setae along right and left posterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[1195,1262,1377,1402]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,231,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1410,195,1950]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Macrostemum bravoi, new species. A, right fore- and hind wings, dorsal view; B – E, male genitalia: B, left lateral view; C, phallus, left lateral view; D, apex of phallus, ventral view; E, terga IX and X, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217689/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Fig. 
<number box="[1248,1262,1378,1402]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Segment X, in dorsal view, bilobed, each lobe apically rounded and with subapical wart (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1101,1413,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,231,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1410,195,1950]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Macrostemum bravoi, new species. A, right fore- and hind wings, dorsal view; B – E, male genitalia: B, left lateral view; C, phallus, left lateral view; D, apex of phallus, ventral view; E, terga IX and X, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217689/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Fig. 
<number box="[1087,1101,1414,1438]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E); in lateral view, tapered to rounded apex, with subdorsal row of small setae 
<number box="[720,734,1449,1474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[743,755,1449,1474]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
rds distance from base and another on ventrolateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,1485,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,231,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1410,195,1950]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Macrostemum bravoi, new species. A, right fore- and hind wings, dorsal view; B – E, male genitalia: B, left lateral view; C, phallus, left lateral view; D, apex of phallus, ventral view; E, terga IX and X, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217689/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Fig. 
<number box="[215,229,1486,1510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Inferior appendages uniformly covered by small setae; each with basal segment approximately same length as apical segment, constricted subbasally; apical segment gradually broader to near rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1401,1521,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,231,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1410,195,1950]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Macrostemum bravoi, new species. A, right fore- and hind wings, dorsal view; B – E, male genitalia: B, left lateral view; C, phallus, left lateral view; D, apex of phallus, ventral view; E, terga IX and X, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217689/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Fig. 
<number box="[1387,1401,1522,1546]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Phallus arched; apex, in lateral view, truncate, with small rounded posteroventral prominence; phallotremal sclerite falciform, without dorsal process, bearing medial prominence on anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1151,1593,1618]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,231,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1410,195,1950]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Macrostemum bravoi, new species. A, right fore- and hind wings, dorsal view; B – E, male genitalia: B, left lateral view; C, phallus, left lateral view; D, apex of phallus, ventral view; E, terga IX and X, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217689/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
Fig. 
<number box="[1137,1151,1594,1618]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C); phallotrema rounded, concave, apically positioned on posterior surface of phallus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
